Class.Name: NSURL
Class.Description: An object that represents the location of a resource, such as an item on a remote server or the path to a local file.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes an NSURL object with a provided URL string.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithString:relativeToURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes an NSURL object with a base URL and a relative string.

InstanceMethods.Name: initFileURLWithPath:isDirectory:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly created NSURL referencing the local file or directory at path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initFileURLWithPath:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly created NSURL referencing the local file or directory at path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initByResolvingBookmarkData:options:relativeToURL:bookmarkDataIsStale:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly created NSURL that points to a location specified by resolving bookmark data.

InstanceMethods.Name: getFileSystemRepresentation:maxLength:
InstanceMethods.Description: Fills the provided buffer with a C string representing a local file system path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initFileURLWithFileSystemRepresentation:isDirectory:relativeToURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a URL object with a C string representing a local file system path.

InstanceMethods.Name: checkResourceIsReachableAndReturnError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns whether the resource pointed to by a file URL can be reached.

InstanceMethods.Name: isFileReferenceURL
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns whether the URL is a file reference URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: resourceValuesForKeys:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the resource values for the properties identified by specified array of keys.

InstanceMethods.Name: getResourceValue:forKey:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value of the resource property for the specified key.

InstanceMethods.Name: setResourceValue:forKey:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the URL’s resource property for a given key to a given value.

InstanceMethods.Name: setResourceValues:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the URL’s resource properties for a given set of keys to a given set of values.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeAllCachedResourceValues
InstanceMethods.Description: Removes all cached resource values and temporary resource values from the URL object.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeCachedResourceValueForKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Removes the cached resource value identified by a given key from the URL object.

InstanceMethods.Name: setTemporaryResourceValue:forKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets a temporary resource value on the URL object.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileReferenceURL
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new file reference URL that points to the same resource as the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: URLByAppendingPathComponent:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new URL made by appending a path component to the original URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: URLByAppendingPathComponent:isDirectory:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new URL made by appending a path component to the original URL, along with a trailing slash if the component is designated a directory.

InstanceMethods.Name: URLByAppendingPathExtension:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new URL made by appending a path extension to the original URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: bookmarkDataWithOptions:includingResourceValuesForKeys:relativeToURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a bookmark for the URL, created with specified options and resource values.

InstanceMethods.Name: startAccessingSecurityScopedResource
InstanceMethods.Description: In an app that has adopted App Sandbox, makes the resource pointed to by a security-scoped URL available to the app.

InstanceMethods.Name: stopAccessingSecurityScopedResource
InstanceMethods.Description: In an app that adopts App Sandbox, revokes access to the resource pointed to by a security-scoped URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: checkPromisedItemIsReachableAndReturnError:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns whether the promised item can be reached.

InstanceMethods.Name: getPromisedItemResourceValue:forKey:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value of the resource property for the specified key.

InstanceMethods.Name: promisedItemResourceValuesForKeys:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the resource values for the properties identified by specified array of keys.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToPasteboard:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the URL to the specified pasteboard.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithScheme:host:path:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly created NSURL with a specified scheme, host, and path.

InstanceMethods.Name: URLHandleUsingCache:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a URL handle to service the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: loadResourceDataNotifyingClient:usingCache:
InstanceMethods.Description: Loads the receiver’s resource data in the background.

InstanceMethods.Name: resourceDataUsingCache:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the receiver’s resource data, loading it if necessary.

InstanceMethods.Name: setResourceData:
InstanceMethods.Description: Attempts to set the resource data for the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: propertyForKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the specified property of the receiver’s resource.

InstanceMethods.Name: setProperty:forKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Changes the specified property of the receiver’s resource.

InstanceProperties.Name: fileURL
InstanceProperties.Description: A boolean value that determines whether the receiver is a file URL.

InstanceProperties.Name: absoluteString
InstanceProperties.Description: The URL string for the receiver as an absolute URL. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: absoluteURL
InstanceProperties.Description: An absolute URL that refers to the same resource as the receiver. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: baseURL
InstanceProperties.Description: The base URL. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: fileSystemRepresentation
InstanceProperties.Description: A C string containing the URL’s file system path. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: fragment
InstanceProperties.Description: The fragment identifier, conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: host
InstanceProperties.Description: The host, conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: lastPathComponent
InstanceProperties.Description: The last path component. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: parameterString
InstanceProperties.Description: The parameter string conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: password
InstanceProperties.Description: The password conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: path
InstanceProperties.Description: The path, conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: pathComponents
InstanceProperties.Description: An array containing the path components. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: pathExtension
InstanceProperties.Description: The path extension. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: port
InstanceProperties.Description: The port, conforming to RFC 1808.

InstanceProperties.Name: query
InstanceProperties.Description: The query string, conforming to RFC 1808.

InstanceProperties.Name: relativePath
InstanceProperties.Description: The relative path, conforming to RFC 1808. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: relativeString
InstanceProperties.Description: A string representation of the relative portion of the URL. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: resourceSpecifier
InstanceProperties.Description: The resource specifier. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: scheme
InstanceProperties.Description: The scheme. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: standardizedURL
InstanceProperties.Description: A copy of the URL with any instances of ".." or "." removed from its path. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: user
InstanceProperties.Description: The user name, conforming to RFC 1808.

InstanceProperties.Name: filePathURL
InstanceProperties.Description: A file path URL that points to the same resource as the URL object. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: URLByDeletingLastPathComponent
InstanceProperties.Description: A URL created by taking the receiver and removing the last path component. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: URLByDeletingPathExtension
InstanceProperties.Description: A URL created by taking the receiver and removing the path extension, if any. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: URLByResolvingSymlinksInPath
InstanceProperties.Description: A URL that points to the same resource as the receiver and includes no symbolic links. (read-only)

InstanceProperties.Name: URLByStandardizingPath
InstanceProperties.Description: A URL that points to the same resource as the original URL using an absolute path. (read-only)

TypeMethods.Name: URLWithString:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an NSURL object initialized with a provided URL string.

TypeMethods.Name: URLWithString:relativeToURL:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an NSURL object initialized with a base URL and a relative string.

TypeMethods.Name: fileURLWithPath:isDirectory:
TypeMethods.Description: Initializes and returns a newly created NSURL object as a file URL with a specified path.

TypeMethods.Name: fileURLWithPath:
TypeMethods.Description: Initializes and returns a newly created NSURL object as a file URL with a specified path.

TypeMethods.Name: fileURLWithPathComponents:
TypeMethods.Description: Initializes and returns a newly created NSURL object as a file URL with specified path components.

TypeMethods.Name: URLByResolvingAliasFileAtURL:options:error:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a new URL made by resolving the alias file at url.

TypeMethods.Name: URLByResolvingBookmarkData:options:relativeToURL:bookmarkDataIsStale:error:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a new URL made by resolving bookmark data.

TypeMethods.Name: fileURLWithFileSystemRepresentation:isDirectory:relativeToURL:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a new URL object initialized with a C string representing a local file system path.

TypeMethods.Name: bookmarkDataWithContentsOfURL:error:
TypeMethods.Description: Initializes and returns bookmark data derived from an alias file pointed to by a specified URL.

TypeMethods.Name: resourceValuesForKeys:fromBookmarkData:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns the resource values for properties identified by a specified array of keys contained in specified bookmark data.

TypeMethods.Name: writeBookmarkData:toURL:options:error:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an alias file on disk at a specified location with specified bookmark data.

TypeMethods.Name: URLFromPasteboard:
TypeMethods.Description: Reads an NSURL object off of the specified pasteboard.
